    <text>
        
        <front>
            <div type="editorial_desc">
                <p>In the cartoon, Theodore Roosevelt is depicted as a bee keeper and wears a shirt with his initials "T.R".  The hive is labeled "G.O.P National Convention" and, below it, there is a sign that reads "indorsement of administration in G.O.P. Platform.</p> 
                <p>The cartoon suggests that Roosevelt knows how to handle his Republican Party.  Before the 1908 presidential election, Roosevelt decided not to run for a third term and, instead, to help his Secretary of War William Taft win the election.  Due to Roosevelt's political support, Taft won his party's nomination and later, the presidential election.</p>
                
            </div>
        </front>

